'''Kitashita Shrine''' (きたしたじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tawaramoto|Q1203159|qid=Q1203159|1=Tawaramoto, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Shiki District|Q1155036|qid=Q1155036|1=Shiki District, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=Shikinai Shōsha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, and its former rank was village shrine.

=== Enshrined deities ===
The following two deities are enshrined.
*{{ill|lt=Ame no Kaguyama no Mikoto|Q10940849|qid=Q10940849|1=Ame-no-Kaguyama}}
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane|qid=Q2564508}}

According to shrine tradition, {{ill|lt=Ame no Kaguyama no Mikoto|Q10940849|qid=Q10940849|1=Ame-no-Kaguyama}} is identified with Ishikoridome-no-Mikoto, and together with {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane|qid=Q2564508}} enshrines the same deities as {{ill|lt=Kagamitsukuri niimasu Amateru Mitama Shrine|Q38278496|qid=Q38278496|1=Kagamitsukuri Nimasu Amateru Mitama Shrine}}. The shrine name "Kitashita" means "the field of the Kita clan," and is interpreted as a deity of metalworkers who forged "kita" (iron). Among the Mononobe Ōki no Muraji clan based in this region, there was the '''Kitashi no Muraji''' (forging lineage), ancestors of the Kagamitsukuri no Muraji, and this shrine is said to have been the one they ritually served.

=== History ===
According to shrine tradition, it was enshrined in the 7th year of {{ill|lt=Emperor Sujin|Q333530|qid=Q333530|1=Emperor Sujin}}. In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, it was listed as a minor shrine of Jōge District.

